<heading id="3E1D4846FFFAFFC5FF71FE08FD61FE5A" bold="true" box="[151,668,474,501]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FF71FE08FD61FE5A" authority="Zilli &amp; Hogenes, 2002" authorityName="Zilli &amp; Hogenes" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,668,474,501]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="treadawayi">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FF71FE08FD61FE5A" bold="true" box="[151,668,474,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FF71FE08FE6FFE5B" bold="true" box="[151,402,474,501]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Eudocima treadawayi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFAFFC5FE7FFE08FD61FE5A" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W." box="[409,668,474,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="153 - 207" refId="ref41799" refString="Zilli, A. &amp; Hogenes, W. (2002) An annotated list of the fruit-piercing moth genus Eudocima Billberg, 1820 (sensu Poole) with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae, Catocalinae). Quadrifina, 5, 153 - 207." type="journal article" year="2002">Zilli &amp; Hogenes, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFAFFC5FF71FE2DFDD3FD63" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFAFFC5FF71FE2DFEECFDB7" blockId="18.[151,1436,474,717]" box="[151,273,511,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFAFFC5FF46FE2DFF0FFDB7" box="[160,242,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="64.[151,250,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[195,1391,191,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-32@64.[189,1399,181,1941]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="FIGURE 11. Eudocima kuehni and Eudocima cocalus group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605524/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
: I)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFAFFC5FF71FDF1FDD3FD63" blockId="18.[151,1436,474,717]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
It is sympatric with similar 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FE30FDF1FDB0FD93" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[470,589,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocalus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FE30FDF1FDB0FD93" box="[470,589,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. cocalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFAFFC5FD79FDF1FCE0FD93" box="[671,797,547,573]" name="Philippines" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Philippines</collectingCountry>
but can be separated by the duller more olive forewing color, and reduced white maculation in the female (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFAFFC5FD3CFD95FC6CFDCF" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[730,913,583,609]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FCF2FD95FCBBFDCF" box="[788,838,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). The pm line of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FBB4FD95FB12FDCF" box="[1106,1263,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="treadawayi">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FBB4FD95FB12FDCF" box="[1106,1263,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. treadawayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctly sinusoidal posterior of vein R5, whereas it is fairly straight in 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FCDDFDB9FC4AFD2B" box="[827,951,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FCDDFDB9FC4EFD2B" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[827,947,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocalus">E. cocalus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FC3AFDB9FBAFFD2B" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[988,1106,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocalus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FC3AFDB9FBAFFD2B" box="[988,1106,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. cocalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pm line is sharply bent at vein R5, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFAFFC5FE98FD5DFDEEFD07" box="[382,531,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="treadaway">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FE98FD5DFDEEFD07" box="[382,531,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. treadaway</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is straight across this vein. It has been recorded from the 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFAFFC5FB53FD5DFA83FD07" box="[1205,1406,655,681]" name="Philippines" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Philippine islands</collectingCountry>
of 
<collectingRegion id="A72E31C8FFFAFFC5FF71FD61FF2AFD63" box="[151,215,691,717]" country="Philippines" name="Southern Leyte" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Leyte</collectingRegion>
and Negros (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFAFFC5FE8BFD61FDDFFD63" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[365,546,691,717]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFAFFC5FE40FD61FE2AFD63" box="[422,471,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
